# Bitbucket Language Scraper

Python CLI project for scraping repository languages from:
- Bitbucket Cloud (`bitbucket.org`)
- Bitbucket Server / Data Center

## Project Structure

```text
.
|-- pyproject.toml
`-- src/
    `-- bitbucket_language_scraper/
        |-- __init__.py
        |-- __main__.py
        `-- cli.py
```

## Install

```powershell
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install -e .
```

## Run

```powershell
bitbucket-language-scraper --help
```

## Usage

Cloud mode:

```powershell
bitbucket-language-scraper `
  --mode cloud `
  --workspace your-workspace `
  --bb-username your-email@example.com `
  --bb-app-password your-app-password
```

Server/Data Center mode:

```powershell
bitbucket-language-scraper `
  --mode server `
  --server-url https://mycompany.fr `
  --server-token your-token `
  --max-workers 8
```

Important:
- If your UI is `https://mycompany.fr/projects`, pass `--server-url https://mycompany.fr`.
- Do not pass `/projects` in `--server-url`.

TLS in corporate environments:

```powershell
bitbucket-language-scraper `
  --mode server `
  --server-url https://mycompany.fr `
  --server-token your-token `
  --ca-bundle C:\path\corp-ca.pem
```

Last resort (temporary only):

```powershell
bitbucket-language-scraper --mode server --server-url https://mycompany.fr --server-token your-token --insecure
```

## Environment Variables

- `BB_WORKSPACE`
- `BB_USERNAME`
- `BB_APP_PASSWORD`
- `BB_SERVER_URL`
- `BB_SERVER_TOKEN`
- `BB_SERVER_USER`
- `BB_SERVER_PASS`
- `BB_CA_BUNDLE`
- `BB_INSECURE`
- `OUTPUT_CSV`
- `OUTPUT_JSON`
- `MAX_WORKERS`

## Output

The scraper writes:
- `bitbucket_languages.csv`
- `bitbucket_languages.json`
